{
  "id": "momentum-volume-compression-001",
  "name": "Volume-Weighted Momentum Compression",
  "description": "This strategy focuses on trading medium-volatility stocks by leveraging shifts in volume-weighted price momentum. It combines the analysis of VWAP and EMA with intraday volatility compression patterns to identify optimal entry points.",
  "algorithm_type": "Momentum",
  "prompt": "I want to design a daily timeframe strategy that trades medium-volatility stocks by exploiting shifts in volume-weighted price momentum combined with intraday volatility compression patterns.\n\nEntry criteria:  \n- Calculate a volume-weighted average price (VWAP) and a 5-day exponential moving average (EMA) of the closing price.  \n- Compute the daily range (High - Low) and apply a 10-day average true range (ATR) to assess recent volatility.  \n- Identify periods when the daily range is below 60% of the 10-day ATR (volatility compression).  \n- Confirm momentum direction by comparing the 5-day EMA to the VWAP: enter long when EMA crosses above VWAP during volatility compression accompanied by rising volume (volume higher than the 5-day average volume). Enter short when EMA crosses below VWAP under the same compression and volume conditions.  \n\nExit criteria:  \n- Exit when the daily range expands beyond 120% of the 10-day ATR (indicating volatility breakout), or  \n- When the EMA crosses back below (for longs) or above (for shorts) the VWAP, or  \n- A fixed stop-loss set at 2% adverse price move from entry.  \n\nThis approach aims to enter trades anticipating expansion following low-volatility consolidation confirmed by sustained volume momentum, capturing directional moves after quiet periods.",
